			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First off, to those of you who ridiculed Rulz.  I read his post.  I read his post, since it started out using a quote from my post.  He did not complain about an inability to play the game.  He only asked if anyone knew of a way for him to configure his computer so it would work.  Some of you are much too ready to criticize.<BR>
<BR>
To Rulz.  In my BIOS, I do not have an ability to disable my on-board video and there are no on-board jumpers.  I do not have an AGP slot and even if I could disable my on-board video, PCI video is not worth it.<BR>
<BR>
And thirdly, calling names to either side of this debate does not make a point nor make you look good.  Zackron's motives are unknown to all of us.<BR>
<BR>
Comparing cars, food, jobs, etc to the computer world is appels and oranges.  Nothing in this world advances or changes as quickly as PCs do.  I suggest to all of you that when you buy any piece of software capable of live patching no matter what the box or disclaimer says, ASSUME THE SPECS WILL CHANGE!  Computer technology drastically changes every 18 months wether Sony/Verant is a part of it or not.<BR>
<BR>
The only thing I think Verant should even TRY to do for their customer base is the same thing Ultima On-line did when they encountered this very similar situation.  If someone from Verant reads this, take this into consideration.  Could one or more servers be brought up separately to support Direct X7.0 and not support the Luclin upgrade.  I see the Luclin advancement as a good thing, but why not set up a server or two for those users who can not or do not wish to upgrade?  <BR>
<BR>
I work in a very fast-paced technological business and I learned that if you see a problem, approach with a solution.<BR>
<BR>
Thanks all<BR>
<BR>
Zallakin DaMaji<BR>
34th Season Magician<BR>
Torvonillous
